                        </support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="leaf"/>
                           <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                              <height/>
                              <width/>
                              <depth/>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                        </seg>
                        <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                        <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#125v"/> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#135v #136r"/> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#iiiv(erso)"/>
                        <desc>
                           <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/>,<persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo"/> and the <term key="dragon"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#ivv(erso)"/>
                        <desc>
                           <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#vr(ecto)"/>
                        <desc>
                           <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/> 
                           <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/> Enthroned</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#vir(ecto)"/>
                        <desc> The Holy Trinity surrounded by <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1096SavioroftheWorld"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#167v"/>
                        <desc> , upper: guardian <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1082Angel"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">
                        <locus target="#167v"/>
                        <desc> , upper: guardian - <locus target="#168r"/>
                           <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d7">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #8v #16r #24v #35r #43r #49v #59r #70v #79r #85r #98v #111r #114r #120v #126v #140r #168v"/> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#1r #8r #42v #49r #84v #98r #126r #139v #161v"/> (line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#53r"/> (line of red dots); <locus target="#110v #120r"/> (multiple full stops between lines of red and black dots).
                    A few of the harags are similar to those produced in the government scriptorium
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="Asmat">
                              <locus target="#98r"/>, lower margin, in red ink: Asmat Prayer to lure a lover, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ መስተፋቅር፡</foreign>. The prayer incorporates a line from a text in Faith of the Fathers. The same prayer is repeated on <locus target="#110v"/>, lower margin
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #ivr(ecto) #vv(erso) #vir(ecto) #viv(erso) #viir(ecto) #viiv(erso)"/>": blank
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                    Upper margins of <locus target="#2r #3r #5r"/>, etc.: Instructions for when to recite certain psalms, written in a later, untrained hand
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                    It is unclear what manuscript this is in the insurance hand list
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>
                    Navigation system:
                    red string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#16"/>;
                    yellow string is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#24 #126"/>; black yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#35 #70 #111 #140"/>;
                    green yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#43 #79r"/>;
                    purple yarn is sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#85"/>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–7
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc>
                    Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                           <desc>
                    Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#11v #33v #34v #80r #95v"/>, etc.); and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#105r #111v"/>); and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#106v"/>, line 22); erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#62"/>r); text has been removed (<locus target="#11v #17v #24r #80r #152r"/>, etc.)
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
